U-Boot for the TQ-Systems TQMa8M[S,D,Q][L][M,N]L SOM and Baseboards

Quick Start
===========
- Build the ARM Trusted firmware binary
- Get ddr fimware
- Build U-Boot
- Boot

Get and Build the ARM Trusted firmware
======================================
Note: srctree is U-Boot source directory
Get ATF from: https://source.codeaurora.org/external/imx/imx-atf
branch: lf-5.4.y
$ make PLAT=imx8m[m,n] bl31
$ cp build/imx8m[m,n]/release/bl31.bin $(srctree)

Get the ddr firmware
=============================
$ wget https://www.nxp.com/lgfiles/NMG/MAD/YOCTO/firmware-imx-8.6.bin
$ chmod +x firmware-imx-8.6.bin
$ ./firmware-imx-8.6.bin
$ cp firmware-imx-8.6/firmware/ddr/synopsys/lpddr4*.bin $(srctree)

Build U-Boot
============
mem: 
* 1gb for 1GB
* 2gb for 2GB

baseboard:
* mba8mx for MBa8Mx starterkit mainboard

$ export CROSS_COMPILE=aarch64-poky-linux-
$ make tqma8mx[m,n]l_<mem>_<baseboard>_mmc_defconfig
$ make flash.bin

Burn the flash.bin to MicroSD card offset 32KB
$sudo dd if=flash.bin of=/dev/sd[x] bs=1k seek=32 conv=fsync

Boot
====
Set Boot switch to Boot from SD-Card to boot from Micro SD.
